                        <provenance type="found">The precise original location is unknown. The stone was found while digging peat in a bog in this townland and was purchased by Cork Public Museum in <date>1940</date> (Macalister 1945, 126). This stone was not included in Canon Power’s account of the ogham stones at University College Cork in 1932, but it was present in 1945 when Macalister published his Corpus.
                        </provenance>
                        <provenance type="observed" when="2024">Now on permanent display in the Stone Corridor (‘Rúin na gCloch / Stories in Stone’ exhibition), University College Cork, where it was examined for the OG(H)AM project in May 2024.</provenance>            
